1.40	Lostock_Hall	Lostock Hall	Lostock Hall ( ) is a small suburban village within the South Ribble borough of Lancashire, England. It is located on the south side of the River Ribble, some 3 miles (4.8 km) south of Preston and 2.5 miles (4 km) north of Leyland. It is bordered on its southeastern side by the interchange for the M6, M61 and M65 motorways. At the time of the United Kingdom Census 2001, the central Lostock Hall area had a population of 3,948.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/73/Lancashire_UK_location_map.svg/240px-Lancashire_UK_location_map.svg.png
